<inglise> - the types and quantities of asbestos used, </inglise>
<eesti> - kasutatud asbesti liigid ja kogused, </eesti>
<inglise> - the activities and processes involved, </inglise>
<eesti> - k&otilde;nealused toimingud ja protsessid, </eesti>
<inglise> - the products manufactured. </inglise>
<eesti> - valmistatud tooted. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Workers and/or their representatives in undertakings or establishments shall have access to the documents which are the subject of notification concerning their own undertaking or establishment in accordance with national laws. </inglise>
<eesti> Ettev&otilde;tete v&otilde;i asutuste t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel ja/v&otilde;i nende esindajatel on siseriikliku &otilde;iguse kohaselt juurdep&auml;&auml;s dokumentidele, mis puudutavad nende ettev&otilde;tte v&otilde;i asutuse kohta esitatud teateid. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> Each time an important change occurs in the use of asbestos or of materials containing asbestos, a new notification must be submitted. </inglise>
<eesti> Iga kord, kui toimub oluline muutus asbesti v&otilde;i asbesti sisaldavate materjalide kasutamises, tuleb esitada uus teade. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> The application of asbestos by means of the spraying process must be prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti> Asbesti pealekandmine pihustamise abil tuleb keelata. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> For all activities referred to in Article 3 (1), the exposure of workers to dust arising from asbestos or materials containing asbestos at the place of work must be reduced to as low a level as is reasonably practicable and in any case below the limit values laid down in Article 8, in particular through the following measures if appropriate: </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;igi artikli 3 l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud toimingute puhul tuleb t&ouml;&ouml;tajate kokkupuude asbestist v&otilde;i asbesti sisaldavatest materjalidest tekkiva tolmuga t&ouml;&ouml;kohas viia nii madalale tasemele, kui tegelikkuses on v&otilde;imalik, ja kokkupuude ei tohi mingil juhul &uuml;letada artiklis 8 s&auml;testatud piirv&auml;&auml;rtusi ning selleks tuleb vajaduse korral kasutada eelk&otilde;ige j&auml;rgmisi meetodeid: </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The quantity of asbestos used in each case must be limited to the minimum quantity which is reasonably practicable. </inglise>
<eesti> Igal &uuml;ksikjuhul kasutatava asbesti kogus ei tohi olla suurem tegelikkuses v&otilde;imalikust miinimumist. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The number of workers exposed or likely to be exposed to dust arising from asbestos or materials containing asbestos must be limited to the lowest possible figure. </inglise>
<eesti> Asbestist v&otilde;i asbesti sisaldavatest materjalidest tekkiva tolmuga kokkupuutuvate v&otilde;i kokku puutuda v&otilde;ivate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate hulk peab olema v&otilde;imalikult v&auml;ike. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Work processes must, in principle, be so designed as to avoid the release of asbestos dust into the air. </inglise>
<eesti> T&ouml;&ouml;protsess tuleb p&otilde;him&otilde;tteliselt kavandada selliselt, et v&auml;ltida asbestitolmu sattumist &otilde;hku. </eesti>
<inglise> If this is not reasonably practicable, the dust should be eliminated as near as possible to the point where it is released. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui see ei ole tegelikkuses v&otilde;imalik, tuleks tolm eemaldada v&otilde;imalikult l&auml;hedal &otilde;hkupaiskumise kohale. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> All buildings and/or plant and equipment involved in the processing or treatment of asbestos must be capable of being regularly and effectively cleaned and maintained. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;iki asbesti tootmise v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisega seotud rajatisi ja/v&otilde;i seadmeid ja masinaid peab saama korrap&auml;raselt ja t&otilde;husalt puhastada ja hooldada. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> Asbestos as a raw material must be stored and transported in suitable sealed packing. </inglise>
<eesti> Toormaterjalina tuleb asbesti s&auml;ilitada ja transportida n&otilde;uetekohastes suletud pakendites. </eesti>
<inglise> 6. </inglise>
<eesti> 6. </eesti>
<inglise> Waste must be collected and removed from the place of work as soon as possible in suitable sealed packing with labels indicating that it contains asbestos. </inglise>
<eesti> J&auml;&auml;tmed tuleb kokku koguda ja v&otilde;imalikult kiiresti t&ouml;&ouml;kohalt k&otilde;rvaldada n&otilde;uetekohastes suletud pakendites, mis on t&auml;histatud siltidega, et nad sisaldavad asbesti. </eesti>
<inglise> This measure shall not apply to mining activities. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda abin&otilde;u ei kohaldata kaevandamise suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> The waste referred to in the preceding paragraph shall then be dealt with in accordance with Council Directive 78/319/EEC of 20 March 1978 on toxic and dangerous waste (1). </inglise>
<eesti> Eelmises l&otilde;ikes osutatud j&auml;&auml;tmed k&auml;ideldakse seej&auml;rel vastavalt n&otilde;ukogu 20. m&auml;rtsi 1978. aasta direktiivile 78/319/EM&Uuml; m&uuml;rgiste ja ohtlike j&auml;&auml;tmete kohta. (7) </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> Subject to Article 3 (3), the following measures shall be taken: </inglise>
<eesti> Arvestades artikli 3 l&otilde;ike 3 s&auml;tteid, v&otilde;etakse j&auml;rgmised meetmed: </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> In order to ensure compliance with the limit values laid down in Article 8, the measurement of asbestos in the air at the place of work shall be carried out in accordance with the reference method described in Annex I or any other method giving equivalent results. </inglise>
<eesti> Et artiklis 8 s&auml;testatud piirv&auml;&auml;rtustest kinnipidamine oleks tagatud, m&otilde;&otilde;detakse asbestisisaldust t&ouml;&ouml;koha &otilde;hus I lisas kirjeldatud standardmeetodiga v&otilde;i muu meetodiga, mis annab samav&auml;&auml;rsed tulemused. </eesti>
<inglise> Such measurement must be planned and carried out regularly, with sampling being representative of the personal exposure of the worker to dust arising from asbestos or materials containing asbestos. </inglise>
<eesti> Selliseid m&otilde;&otilde;tmisi tuleb kavandada ja teostada korrap&auml;raselt ning v&otilde;etud proovid peavad iseloomustama t&ouml;&ouml;taja kokkupuudet asbestist v&otilde;i asbesti sisaldavatest materjalidest tekkiva tolmuga. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of measuring asbestos in the air, as referred to in the preceding paragraph, only fibres with a length of more than five micrometres and a length/breadth ratio greater than 3: 1 shall be taken into consideration. </inglise>
<eesti> Eelmises l&otilde;ikes nimetatud asbestisisalduse kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramiseks &otilde;hus v&otilde;etakse arvesse ainult neid kiude, mis on v&auml;hemalt viis mikromeetrit pikad ja mille pikkuse/laiuse suhe on suurem kui 3: 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The Council, acting on a proposal from the Commission, and taking account in particular of progress made in scientific knowledge and technology and of experience gained in the application of this Directive, shall re-examine the provisions of the first sentence of paragraph 1 within five years following the adoption of this Directive, with a view to establishing a single method for measurement of asbestos-in-air concentrations at Community level. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni ettepanekul ning v&otilde;ttes arvesse eelk&otilde;ige teaduse ja tehnika arengut ja k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaldamisel omandatud kogemusi, vaatab n&otilde;ukogu l&otilde;ike 1 esimeses lauses s&auml;testatu l&auml;bi viie aasta jooksul p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva direktiivi vastuv&otilde;tmist, et kehtestada &uuml;henduse tasandil &uuml;htne meetod asbestisisalduse m&otilde;&otilde;tmiseks &otilde;hus. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Sampling shall be carried out after consulting the workers and/or their representatives in undertakings or establishments. </inglise>
